SOULFUL singer Lady Donli recently put on a stellar performance alongside ‘The Lagos Panic band at the Alliance Francaise Mike Adenuga Centre. Donli, in her style, thrilled guests with renditions of her songs that include ‘Cash’, ‘Suffer Suffer’, ‘Corner’, and other songs from her album, ‘Enjoy Your Life.’   Monalisa Chinda: My plan to celebrate West African heritage     Real Housewives of Lagos: Laura, Carolyna take animosity to…     Burna Boy: Back in trouble with the law   During her performance, Donli was joined by Tomi Thomas for a boisterous performance of their collaboration, ‘Ice Cream’. During the singer’s performance, Lady Donli’s manager, Opus said, “Donli is a stickler for perfection as far as her craft is concerned. She is an artist who respects the art form and will not compromise on any aspects including the art of performance.”